Name: embryonal rhabdomyosarcoma
Definition: A rhabdomyosarcoma wherein the mesenchymally-derived malignant cells resemble the primitive developing skeletal muscle of the embryo; it occurs most often in the head and neck area or in the genital or urinary organs.

Name: pleomorphic rhabdomyosarcoma
Definition: A skeletal muscle cancer that arise from skeletal muscle progenitors.

Name: mediastinum rhabdomyosarcoma
Definition: A rhabdomyosarcoma that is located_in the mediastinum and affects children and adolescents.

Name: alveolar rhabdomyosarcoma
Definition: A sarcoma and malignant mediastinal mesenchymnal tumor that is located_in the mediastinum.

Name: obsolete rhabdomyosarcoma recurrent
Definition: A sarcoma and malignant mediastinal mesenchymnal tumor that is located_in the mediastinum.

Name: gallbladder rhabdomyosarcoma
Definition: A gallbladder sarcoma that is located_in the gallbladder that has_material_basis_in cells that normally develop into skeletal (voluntary) muscles.

Name: ovary rhabdomyosarcoma
Definition: An ovary sarcoma that arises from skeletal muscle progenitors.

Name: mixed type rhabdomyosarcoma
Definition: A sarcoma and malignant tumor of extrahepatic bile duct that is located_in the bile duct.

Name: anus rhabdomyosarcoma
Definition: A rhabdomyosarcoma and sarcoma of the anus that is located_in the anus.
